<br>
We enter a dark misty woods, and its really hard to see the path with the torches off.  Its a good thing she was leading by quite a bit because just as the woods was thinning and we thought we were out, 5 or 6 Siabra (evil elves) Waylayers that were way purple to us swarmed out and killed her. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I told her I'd edge in there and res her when they left, and she told me to forget it.  In the little circle of trees there, EACH ONE had a waylayer.  This had to be the absolute best time dying she ever had...just the set up of it: you had to be concentrating on the road so you didn't lose it, and then if you weren't distracted enough already you see that you are almost out of the woods and BAM!<br>
<br>
She said afterwards she should have known from the 4 gravestones that something was up. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src="http://rass7th.homestead.com/Files/rassig.gif">
