<br>
Watch out for Luch Catchers (agressive cats), beetles, and Irewood Saplings (very hard to see in the woods).<br>
<br>
Also, when you do the next part, going to see the named Merman, don't go at night!  There's about 20 times more aggressive purple mobs out there.  I tried and died, and then went in the day and the only thing you have to worry about then are the aggressive Pookas (horses) near the merman lake. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/urassaths.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rassaths</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 750<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(11/14/01 3:06:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=198.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://rass7th.homestead.com/Files/rassface3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yah, we got the correct fork in the road...</span><hr size=1> ...the 2nd time we tried it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
